      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments conducted at 37 °C with bovine blood analogue (glycerol-water, viscosity matched). Flow rates 2.5–6.0 L/min and speeds 2000–3500 rpm bracket the COU operating envelope. Temperature, fluid batch, and hematocrit (40%) recorded per ASTM F1841. Test conditions adequately represent COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined; model predictions within acceptance band for primary QoI across validation cases.",
      "rationale": "NIH comparison uses relative error metric with acceptance band ±10%. All five operating points satisfy criterion (max relative error 4.7%). Pressure-rise comparison uses RMS error < 5% criterion; achieved 3.1%. Output comparison demonstrates adequate model fidelity for COU decision."
    },
    {
