      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations and constitutive models (turbulence, hemolysis power-law) justified for the flow regime and QoI; alternative model forms considered.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published comparative studies for confined impeller flows (Giersiepen et al.; Taskin et al.). Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen 1990) with Lagrangian particle tracking used for NIH; recognised as standard approach for MRL 2 assessment. Reynolds number range (Re 3,000–25,000) within validated applicability domain. Model form adequacy confirmed."
    },
