    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Three validation activities demonstrate model fidelity within acceptance criteria across the COU operating envelope. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo and GCI confirms NIH predictions remain below RH = 1 acceptance threshold including worst-case geometric tolerance variation. Six factors not assessed are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
